ivardefs.name: authority
ivardefs.desc: Indicates the authority who published the protocol.  E.g. ACIP.

ivardefs.name: description
ivardefs.desc: Contains the description about the protocol under which the vaccine was administered.

ivardefs.name: doseStatus
ivardefs.desc: Indicates if the immunization event should "count" against  the protocol.

ivardefs.name: doseStatusReason
ivardefs.desc: Provides an explanation as to why an immunization event should or should not count against the protocol.

ivardefs.name: series
ivardefs.desc: One possible path to achieve presumed immunity against a disease - within the context of an authority.

ivardefs.name: seriesDoses
ivardefs.desc: The recommended number of doses to achieve immunity.

properties.desc: Contains information about the protocol(s) under which the vaccine was administered.
